2%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65046628b8708d001927b4d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOregon's%20state%20capitol%20in%20Salem.%3Cp%3EEducation%20Images%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEvery%20US%20state%20has%20a%20capitol%20that%20houses%20its%20state%20legislature.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMany%20state%20capitols%20are%20domed%20buildings%20similar%20to%20the%20US%20capitol%2C%20but%20others%20are%20more%20unique.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMaryland's%20State%20House%20is%20the%20oldest%20capitol%20in%20continuous%20legislative%20use%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20state's%20capitol%20is%20an%20important%20structure%3A%20It%20signifies%20the%20state%20government's%20power%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-weird-fact-about-every-state-2017-9%5C%22%3Estate's%20history%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20its%20people%20and%20any%20who%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20states'%20capitols%20have%20unique%20references%20to%20history%20or%20location%2C%20like%20Kansas'%20statue%20of%20a%20Kansa%20warrior%20atop%20its%20dome%2C%20or%20the%20New%20Hampshire%20State%20House%20which%20was%20built%20with%20locally%20sourced%20granite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20history%2C%20the%20structures%20have%20also%20proven%20costly.%20When%20New%20York's%20state%20capitol%20in%20Albany%20was%20finally%20finished%20after%2032%20years%20in%201899%2C%20it%20was%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20%2425%20million%2C%20making%20it%20one%20of%20the%20most%20expensive%20government%20projects%20in%20the%20US.%20In%202013%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.nytimes.com%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2013%2F03%2F10%2Fnyregion%2Fa-tour-of-the-new-york-state-capitol.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20the%20figure%20was%20equivalent%20to%20more%20than%20half%20a%20billion%20dollars%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20capitol%20building%20has%20a%20unique%20look%20and%20distinct%20origin%2C%20and%20you%20can%20learn%20more%20about%20them%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMontgomery%2C%20Alabama%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225662%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22alabama%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ef9f8044dca6806575a1225%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223189%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlabama's%20capitol%20in%20Montgomery.%3Cp%3ECarol%20M.%20Highsmith%2FBuyenlarge%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlabama's%20capitol%20is%20also%20where%20the%20Confederacy%20began%2C%20and%20there's%20a%20brass%20star%20on%20one%20of%20the%20porticos%20marking%20the%20spot%20where%20Jefferson%20Davis%20was%20sworn%20in%20as%20its%20president%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fahc.alabama.gov%2Falabama-state-capitol.aspx%5C%22%3EAlabama%20Historical%20Commission.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20building%20that%20stands%20today%20was%20constructed%20in%201851%2C%20after%20a%20fire%20burned%20down%20the%20original%20building%20in%201849%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Alabama%20Historical%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20more%20famous%20parts%20of%20the%20capitol%20grounds%20is%20the%20Avenue%20of%20Flags.%20It%20has%20the%20flag%20of%20every%20state%20plus%20a%20native%20rock%20from%20each%20state%20at%20each%20flag's%20base.%20It%20was%20dedicated%20in%201968%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fexploringmontgomery.com%2Favenue-of-flags%2F%5C%22%3EExploring%20Montgomery.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJuneau%2C%20Alaska%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221566%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22alaska%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ef9fac33ad861088e04c544%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221175%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlaska's%20capitol%20in%20Juneau.%3Cp%3EGoogle%20Maps%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Alaska%20State%20Capitol%2C%20completed%20in%201931%2C%20doesn't%20look%20much%20different%20from%20any%20other%20office%20building%20in%20Juneau%2C%20save%20the%20marble%20columns.%20According%20to%20Alaska's%20official%20website%2C%20it%20is%20one%20of%20few%20state%20capitols%20to%20not%20feature%20a%20dome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1981%2F06%2F14%2Fus%2Falaskans-delaying-on-shift-of-capital.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20in%201981%2C%20neither%20the%20building%20nor%20the%20location%20were%20popular%20with%20locals%20%E2%80%94%20both%20were%20chosen%20because%20the%20residents%20of%20Alaska%20had%20to%20fund%20construction%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20but%20efforts%20to%20move%20the%20capitol%20have%20failed%2C%20even%20though%20a%20vote%20passed%20to%20move%20the%20location%20in%20the%20'70s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20recently%20as%202022%2C%20Alaskan%20senators%20sponsored%20a%20bill%20to%20move%20the%20capital%2C%20this%20time%20to%20Willow%2C%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Falaskapublic.org%2F2022%2F02%2F11%2Fstate-reps-kurka-and-eastman-sponsor-bill-to-move-the-capital-from-juneau-to-willow%2F%5C%22%3EAlaska%20Public%20Media%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20for%20now%2C%20Juneau%20remains%20the%20Last%20Frontier's%20capital%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPhoenix%2C%20Arizona%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22arizona%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ef9fb84aee6a87e384fb85a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222868%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Arizona%20Capitol%20Museum%20in%20Phoenix.%3Cp%3EVisions%20of%20America%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fplace%2FPhoenix-Arizona%2FCultural-life%23ref919463%5C%22%3EEncyclopedia%20Britannica%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Arizona's%20capitol%20was%20dedicated%20in%201901.%20It%20stopped%20being%20the%20home%20of%20the%20legislative%20branches%20of%20government%20in%201960%20%E2%80%94%20and%20by%201978%2C%20all%20government%20officials%20had%20been%20moved%20to%20other%20buildings%20nearby%20in%20an%20area%20called%20the%20Capitol%20Complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20original%20building%20was%20then%20officially%20converted%20into%20a%20museum%20that%20anyone%20can%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELittle%20Rock%2C%20Arkansas%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224533%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22arkansas%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F608857070da8f40018033c60%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArkansas'%20capitol%20in%20Little%20Rock.%3Cp%3EDon%20%26amp%3B%20Melinda%20Crawford%2FEducation%20Images%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EArkansas'%20capitol%20took%2016%20years%20to%20complete.%20Construction%20lasted%20from%201899%20to%201915%2C%20and%20the%20building%20was%20designed%20by%20architects%20George%20R.%20Mann%20and%20Cass%20Gilbert%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fencyclopediaofarkansas.net%2Fentries%2Farkansas-state-capitol-building-377%2F%5C%22%3EEncyclopedia%20of%20Arkansas.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20building%20replaced%20the%20State%20House%2C%20which%20is%20now%20the%20Old%20State%20House%20Museum%2C%20according%20to%20Arkansas%20Heritage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESacramento%2C%20California%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222620%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22california%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa017ff34d05316220a326%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221965%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECalifornia's%20capitol%20in%20Sacramento.%3Cp%3EDavid%20Paul%20Morris%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20building%20was%20constructed%20between%201860%20and%201874%2C%20and%20designed%20by%20Reuben%20S.%20Clark%2C%20and%20it%20has%20been%20listed%20as%20a%20California%20Historical%20Landmark%20since%201974%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcapitolcommission.legislature.ca.gov%2Fhistory%2Fhistory-state-capitol-building%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHistoric%20State%20Capitol%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20design%20was%20based%20on%20the%20US%20Capitol%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20among%20other%20well-known%20American%20buildings%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcapitolmuseum.ca.gov%2Flearn%2Fabout-the-capitol%2Fhistory-of-the-capitol%2Fplanning%2F%5C%22%3EState%20of%20California%20Capitol%20Museum.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20California%20State%20Capitol%20is%20located%20inside%20the%2040-acre%20Capitol%20Park%2C%20which%20contains%20trees%20from%20around%20the%20world%2C%20a%20World%20Peace%20Rose%20Garden%2C%20and%20the%20Civil%20War%20Memorial%20Grove.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDenver%2C%20Colorado%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22907%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22colorado%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa17b0f0f419201c6a7e7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EColorado's%20capitol%20in%20Denver.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Moore%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Colorado%20Capitol%2C%20which%20was%20completed%20in%201901%2C%20was%20also%20designed%20to%20look%20like%20the%20US%20Capitol%2C%20but%20with%20a%20Colorado%20twist%3A%20The%20dome%20is%20covered%20in%20real%20gold%20leaf%20donated%20by%20gold%20miners%20to%20reference%20the%20Colorado%20Gold%20Rush%20from%201858%20to%201861%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fleg.colorado.gov%2FVisit-Learn%5C%22%3EColorado%20General%20Assembly%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHartford%2C%20Connecticut%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223193%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22connecticut%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa26cd5af6cc048e793cc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222395%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EConnecticut's%20capitol%20in%20Hartford.%3Cp%3ERolf%20Schulten%2Fullstein%20bild%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20Connecticut%20State%20Capitol%20is%20actually%20the%20third%20capitol%20the%20state%20has%20had%20since%20the%20American%20Revolution.%20This%20one%2C%20designed%20by%20Richard%20M.%20Upjohn%2C%20opened%20in%201879%2C%20according%20to%20Connecticut's%20official%20state%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20golden%20dome%20is%20surrounded%20by%20six%20pairs%20of%20statues%20representing%20agriculture%2C%20commerce%2C%20education%20and%20law%2C%20force%20and%20war%2C%20science%20and%20justice%2C%20and%20music%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cga.ct.gov%2Fcprc%2Fhistory.asp%5C%22%3EState%20Capitol%20Preservation%20%26amp%3B%20Restoration%20Commission.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDover%2C%20Delaware%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223259%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22delaware%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa289a3f73703adf2db0b3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222444%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDelaware's%20Legislative%20Hall%20in%20Dover.%3Cp%3EHarvey%20Meston%2FArchive%20Photos%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Delaware%20Legislative%20Hall%20was%20dedicated%20in%201933%20and%20replaced%20the%20Old%20State%20House%2C%20which%20is%20opposite%20the%20Hall%20on%20the%20capitol%20mall.%20It%20was%20designed%20in%20the%20Colonial%20Revival%20style%20by%20E.%20William%20Martin%2C%20according%20to%20Delaware's%20official%20state%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWashington%2C%20DC%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222612%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22us%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa28caf0f4192c6b3f0fa9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221959%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20Capitol.%3Cp%3EStefan%20Zaklin%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20Capitol%20is%20located%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%20in%20DC.%20It%20was%20in%20construction%20for%20decades%2C%20partially%20destroyed%20in%201814%2C%20and%20then%20finally%20finished%20in%201829%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aoc.gov%2Fexplore-capitol-campus%2Fbuildings-grounds%2Fcapitol-building%2Fhistory%5C%22%3EArchitect%20of%20the%20Capitol.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0The%20famous%2C%20gigantic%20dome%20was%20later%20added%20during%20an%20expansive%20addition%20in%201855%2C%20designed%20by%20Thomas%20U.%20Walter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAtop%20the%20dome%20sits%20the%20%26quot%3BStatue%20of%20Freedom%2C%26quot%3B%20a%2019-foot%20statue%20of%20a%20woman%20wearing%20a%20battle%20helmet%2C%20holding%20a%20sheathed%20sword%20in%20one%20hand%2C%20and%20a%20laurel%20wreath%20and%20shield%20in%20the%20other.%20She's%20been%20there%20since%201863%2C%20according%20to%20Architect%20of%20the%20Capitol.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visitthecapitol.gov%2Fplan-visit%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETallahassee%2C%20Florida%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223519%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22florida%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa2af35af6cc07363ebe66%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222639%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFlorida's%20capitol%20in%20Tallahassee.%3Cp%3EMark%20Wallheiser%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20capitol%2C%20also%20called%20the%20New%20Capitol%2C%20is%20located%20directly%20in%20front%20of%20the%20original.%20Together%2C%20they%20form%20the%20Capitol%20Complex.%20The%20New%20Capitol%20was%20built%20in%201977%20by%20architect%20Edward%20Durell%20Stone%20and%20the%20firm%20of%20Reynolds%2C%20Smith%2C%20and%20Hills%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Florida%20Capitol%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20website%20reports%20the%20building%20was%20designed%20in%20an%20%26quot%3Binternational%20style%20to%20reflect%20a%20modern%20Florida%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20includes%20a%2022-story%20central%20tower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Old%20Capitol%20still%20stands%2C%20and%20it%20was%20restored%20to%20its%20original%201902%20glory%20in%20the%20'80s.%20Currently%2C%20the%20building%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flhistoriccapitol.gov%2F%5C%22%3EFlorida%20Historic%20Capitol%20Museum.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAtlanta%2C%20Georgia%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222450%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22georgia%20state%20capitol%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa2d7a988ee356d44d52bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221838%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGeorgia's%20capitol%20in%20Atlanta.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Fleming%2FCorbis%2FVCG%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGeorgia's%20capitol%20was%20finished%20in%201889%20and%20designed%20by%20Willoughby%20J.%20Edbrooke%20and%20Franklin%20P.%20Burnham%2C%20according%20to%20the%20city%20of%20Atlanta's%20website.%20It%20sits%20on%20the%20site%20of%20the%20former%20Atlanta%20City%20Hall%2FFulton%20County%20Courthouse%2C%20which%20was%20there%20from%201854%20to%201994.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20city%2C%20it's%20one%20of%2043%20National%20Historic%20Landmarks%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHonolulu%2C%20Hawaii%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hawaii%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa2f00f0f4192fec7298da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHawaii's%20capitol%20in%20Honolulu.%3Cp%3ERolf%20Schulten%2Fullstein%20bild%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20dedication%20of%20the%20Hawaiian%20capitol%20in%201969%2C%20then-Governor%20John%20A.%20Burns%20explained%20the%20design%20of%20the%20building%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2240%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.staradvertiser.com%2F2018%2F01%2F14%2Ftravel%2Fhawaiis-backyard%2Fstate-capitol-shares-lessons-in-art-culture-history-and-aloha%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Honolulu%20Star%20Advertiser%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20this%20great%20State%20Capitol%20there%20are%20no%20doors%20at%20the%20grand%20entrances%20which%20open%20toward%20the%20mountains%20and%20toward%20the%20sea%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20roof%20or%20dome%20to%20separate%20its%20vast%20inner%20court%20from%20the%20heavens%20and%20from%20the%20same%20eternal%20stars%20which%20guided%20the%20first%20voyagers%20to%20the%20primeval%20beauty%20of%20these%20shores.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20building%20is%20also%20surrounded%20by%20a%20reflecting%20pool%20meant%20to%20symbolize%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%2C%20which%20surrounds%20the%20chain%20of%20137%20recognized%20islands%20that%20make%20up%20Hawaii%2C%20according%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2240%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.hawaii.gov%2Fdbedt%2Feconomic%2Flibrary%2Ffacts%2FFacts_Figures_browsable.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20State%20of%20Hawaii.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBoise%2C%20Idaho%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224214%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22idaho%20state%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa33264dca6829f6166145%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIdaho's%20capitol%20in%20Boise.%3Cp%3EEducation%20Images%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIdaho's%20capitol%20was%20designed%20by%20architects%20J.E.%20Tourtellotte%20and%20Charles%20Hummel%2C%20and%20was%20constructed%20between%201905%20and%201920.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcapitolcommission.idaho.gov%2Feducation%2Ffacts-about-the-idaho-capitol-building%2F%5C%22%3EIdaho's%20Capitol%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20the%20only%20capitol%20in%20the%20US%20that%20is%20heated%20by%20geothermal%20water.%20It%20comes%20from%20a%20spring%203%2C000%20feet%20underground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESpringfield%2C%20Illinois%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221689%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22illinois%20state%20capitol%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa328b4dca68298931da83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221267%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIllinois'%20capitol%20in%20Springfield.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Acker%20for%20The%20Washington%20Post%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20pamphlet%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilsos.gov%2Fpublications%2Fpdf_publications%2Fcom18.pdf%5C%22%3EIllinois%20Secretary%20of%20State's%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20current%20capitol%20(the%20state's%20sixth)%20was%20completed%20in%201888%2C%2020%20years%20after%20crews%20broke%20ground.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20its%20construction%2C%20the%20limestone%20dome%20was%20illuminated%20by%20144%20gas%20jets.%20However%2C%20the%20carbon%20emitted%20by%20those%20jets%20eventually%20turned%20the%20dome%20black.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20100%20years%2C%20but%20it%20was%20finally%20cleaned%20in%201986.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIndianapolis%2C%20Indiana%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223546%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22indiana%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa380c3f737041e76f7783%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222659%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIndiana's%20capitol%20in%20Indianapolis.%3Cp%3EEducation%20Images%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.in.gov%2Fidoa%2Fstatehouse%2Fthe-statehouse-story%2F%5C%22%3EIndiana%20Department%20of%20Administration%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Indiana's%20capitol%20was%20completed%20in%201888%2C%20and%20is%20home%20to%20all%20executive%20offices%2C%20the%20Indiana%20State%20Senate%2C%20the%20Indiana%20House%20of%20Representatives%2C%20and%20the%20Indiana%20State%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20among%20others.%20It%20was%20constructed%20with%20Indiana%20limestone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDes%20Moines%2C%20Iowa%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223090%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22iowa%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa3adf4dca682e7f07ed74%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222318%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIowa's%20capitol%20in%20Des%20Moines.%3Cp%3ECarol%20M.%20Highsmith%2FBuyenlarge%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20large%20golden%20dome%20is%2023%20carats%2C%20and%20the%20entire%20building%20is%20275%20feet%20tall%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.legis.iowa.gov%2Fdocs%2Fpublications%2FIF%2F793559.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evisitor's%20guide%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20been%20re-gilded%20four%20times%20since%20its%20construction%20in%201886.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20Iowa's%20capitol%20has%20a%20total%20of%20five%20domes%2C%20making%20it%20the%20only%20capitol%20in%20the%20US%20with%20five.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETopeka%2C%20Kansas%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225406%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kansas%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa3bb01918243718611625%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223562%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EState%20capitol%20in%20Topeka.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Sohm%2FVisions%20of%20America%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKansas'%20capitol%20dome%20is%20topped%20with%20a%20statue%20called%20%26quot%3BAd%20astra%26quot%3B%20(Latin%20for%20%26quot%3Bto%20the%20stars%26quot%3B)%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20state's%20motto%2C%20%26quot%3Bad%20astra%20per%20aspera%26quot%3B%20(%26quot%3Bto%20the%20stars%20through%20difficulties%26quot%3B)%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kshs.org%2Fkansapedia%2Fkansas-state-capitol-ad-astra%2F11742%5C%22%3EKansas%20Historical%20Society.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20statue%20itself%20is%20a%20bronze%20depiction%20of%20a%20warrior%20from%20the%20Kansa%20tribe%20(also%20known%20as%20the%20Kaw%20Nation%20or%20Kanza)%2C%20who%20call%20Kansas%20home%20and%20gave%20the%20state%20its%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20building%20took%2037%20years%20to%20construct%2C%20also%20according%20to%20the%20Kansas%20Historical%20Society%2C%20from%201866%20to%201903.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFrankfort%2C%20Kentucky%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221650%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kentucky%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa3e9bf0f419379a04d2d3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221238%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKentucky's%20capitol%20in%20Frankfort.%3Cp%3EBill%20Pugliano%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKentucky's%20capitol%20was%20designed%20by%20Frank%20Mills%20Andrews%2C%20according%20to%20Kentucky's%20official%20state%20website.%20There%20are%20also%20statues%20lining%20the%20front%20portico%20that%20represent%20Kentucky%2C%20the%20central%20figure%2C%20with%20Progress%2C%20History%2C%20Plenty%2C%20Law%2C%20Art%2C%20and%20Labor%20as%20her%20%26quot%3Battendants%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20state%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20building%20is%20the%20fourth%20capitol%20in%20the%20state%2C%20and%20it%20was%20completed%20in%201910.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBaton%20Rouge%2C%20Louisiana%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223237%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22louisiana%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa3fe1988ee360b3109513%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222428%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELouisiana's%20capitol%20in%20Baton%20Rouge.%3Cp%3EDavid%20LEFRANC%2FGamma-Rapho%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Louisiana%20Capitol%20is%20just%20one%20of%20nine%20capitols%20in%20the%20US%20that%20doesn't%20feature%20a%20dome%20%E2%80%94%20and%20at%20450%20feet%20tall%20(or%2034%20floors)%2C%20it's%20also%20the%20tallest%20capitol%20in%20the%20country%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhouse.louisiana.gov%2Fpubinfo%2FVirtualTour%2Flacaphistory.htm%5C%22%3ELouisiana's%20House%20of%20Representatives.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20dedicated%20in%201932%2C%20without%20the%20person%20who%20had%20spearheaded%20the%20effort%20to%20build%20it%2C%20Senator%20Huey%20P.%20Long%2C%20a%20controversial%20figure%20in%20Louisiana's%20history%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fbiography%2FHuey-Long-American-politician%5C%22%3EEncyclopedia%20Britannica.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAugusta%2C%20Maine%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222004%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22maine%20capitol%20buildings%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa40242618b947f3261faa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221503%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Maine%20State%20House%20in%20Augusta.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Phelan%2FPortland%20Press%20Herald%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20capital%20of%20Maine%20was%20originally%20Portland%20when%20the%20state%20broke%20away%20from%20Massachusetts%20in%201820.%20But%20when%20Mainers%20asked%20for%20a%20more%20centrally%20located%20capital%20city%2C%20Augusta%20was%20chosen%20in%201827%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flegislature.maine.gov%2Fgeneral%2Fhistory-of-the-state-house%2F9137%5C%22%3EMaine%20State%20Legislature%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20building%20was%20completed%20by%201832.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20State%20House's%20dome%20is%20topped%20with%20a%20female%20figure%20of%20Wisdom%2C%20which%20was%20designed%20by%20sculptor%20W.%20Clark%20Noble%20of%20Gardiner%2C%20a%20town%206%20miles%20from%20Augusta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAnnapolis%2C%20Maryland%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224282%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22maryland%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa433ef34d0555123541c9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223212%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMaryland's%20state%20capitol%20in%20Annapolis.%3Cp%3EEducation%20Images%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMaryland's%20State%20House%20is%20the%20oldest%20capitol%20in%20continuous%20legislative%20use%20in%20the%20US%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmsa.maryland.gov%2Fmsa%2Fmdstatehouse%2Fhtml%2Fabout.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilt%20in%201779%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20its%20official%20website.%20It's%20also%20the%20only%20state%20capitol%20to%20have%20once%20served%20as%20the%20US%20capitol%20when%20the%20Continental%20Congress%20met%20there%20from%201783%20to%201784%2C%20according%20to%20the%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBoston%2C%20Massachusetts%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222877%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22massachusetts%20state%20house%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa43d7aee6a82a04777c44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222158%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Old%20State%20House%20for%20the%20Commonwealth%20of%20Massachusetts%20in%20Boston.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Sohm%2FVisions%20of%20America%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Massachusetts%20State%20House%2C%20built%20in%201789%2C%20originally%20had%20a%20wooden%20dome%2C%20but%20Paul%20Revere's%20own%20company%20was%20responsible%20for%20covering%20it%20in%20copper%20in%201802%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fboston%2Fnews%2F5-things-you-didnt-know-about-the-massachusetts-state-house%2F%5C%22%3ECBS%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20land%20it%20was%20built%20on%3F%20It%20used%20to%20be%20owned%20by%20none%20other%20than%20John%20Hancock%2C%20who%20was%20Massachusetts'%20first%20elected%20governor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELansing%2C%20Michigan%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222967%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22michigan%20state%20capitol%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa56a83f737055771eaa07%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222225%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichigan's%20capitol%20in%20Lansing.%3Cp%3EBettman%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20floors%20of%20Michigan's%20capitol%2C%20which%20was%20dedicated%20in%201879%2C%20are%20made%20of%20limestone%20and%20have%20visible%20fossils%20in%20them%2C%20as%20you%20can%20see%20on%20the%20capitol's%20official%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESt.%20Paul%2C%20Minnesota%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223906%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22minnesota%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa5efc3f73705b400846cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222930%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMinnesota's%20capitol%20in%20St.%20Paul.%3Cp%3ERaymond%20Boyd%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.exploreminnesota.com%2Fprofile%2Fminnesota-state-capitol%2F2229%5C%22%3EExplore%20Minnesota%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20state's%20capitol%20is%20the%20second-largest%20self-supporting%20marble%20dome%20in%20the%20world%2C%20only%20behind%20St.%20Peter's%20Basilica%20in%20Rome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArchitect%20Cass%20Gilbert%20insisted%20on%20using%20Georgia%20marble%20for%20the%20dome%2C%20according%20to%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mnhs.org%2Fcapitol%2Flearn%2Farchitecture%5C%22%3E%20Minnesota%20Historical%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20were%20critical%20of%20using%20out-of-state%20materials%2C%20so%20as%20a%20compromise%2C%20the%20contractor%20leased%20the%20quarry%20in%20Georgia%20and%20imported%20the%20rough%20marble%20so%20Minnesotans%20could%20do%20the%20work%20in-state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20nine%20years%2C%20but%20was%20completed%20in%201905.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJackson%2C%20Mississippi%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223001%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mississippi%20capitol%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa5f5a988ee3778c778f45%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMississippi's%20state%20capitol%20in%20Jackson.%3Cp%3ERORY%20DOYLE%2FAFP%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDesigned%20by%20architect%20Theodore%20Link%20and%20constructed%20between%201901%20and%201903%2C%20Mississippi's%20state%20capitol%20was%20built%20on%20the%20site%20of%20an%20old%20state%20penitentiary%2C%20according%20to%20the%20state%20capitol's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.legislature.ms.gov%2Fabout-the-capitol%2Fhistory-of-the-capitol%2F%5C%22%3Eofficial%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20building%20spans%20171%2C000%20square%20feet%20and%20features%204%2C750%20original%20electric%20light%20fixtures%2C%20as%20well%20as%20an%208-foot%20statue%20of%20an%20eagle%20on%20the%20top%20of%20its%20dome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJefferson%20City%2C%20Missouri%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223605%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22GettyImages%20515395544%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa5fd8f34d05683c0c8d0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222704%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMissouri's%20capitol%20in%20Jefferson%20City.%3Cp%3EBettman%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMissouri's%20state%20capitol%20was%20completed%20in%201917%2C%20according%20to%20its%20official%20website.%20Ceres%2C%20the%20goddess%20of%20grain%2C%20sits%20at%20the%20top%20of%20its%20dome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20Missouri's%20state%20legislature%2C%20the%20500%2C000-square-foot%20building%20houses%20the%20Missouri%20State%20Museum%20with%20exhibits%20about%20the%20state's%20history%20and%20natural%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHelena%2C%20Montana%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223740%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22montana%20state%20capitol%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5efa6016f34d05688d6e0475%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222805%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMontana's%20state%20capitol%20in%20Helena.%3Cp%3EEducation%20Images%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20building%20of%20Montana's%20state%20capitol%20was%20completed%20in%201902%2C%20and%20its%20two%20wings%20were%20added%20in%201911%20and%201912%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmhs.mt.gov%2Feducation%2FCapitol%2FCapitol-Art%2F%5C%22%3EMontana%20Historical%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Inside%2C%20the%20building%20features%20works%20of%20art%20such%20as%20the%20mural%20%26quot%3BLewis%20and%20Clark%20Meeting%20Indians%20at%20Ross'%20Hole%2C%26qu